A = (a_1 , a_2) , B = (b_1 , b_2)
(b_1 - a_1 , b_2 - a_2)
\sqrt{(b_1 - a_1)^2 + (b_2 - a_2)^2} = M
\angle V_{B'}
arccos(\frac{b_1 - a_1}{M}) = b
V_{B'}=<b_1 - a_1 , b_2 - a_2>
<M cos(b) , M sin(b)>
V_{left}
V_{right}
=V_{B} +V_{left}
=V_B + V_{right}
V_{right} = <S *cos(b + \pi - a) , S * sin(b + \pi - a)>
V_{left}=<S *cos(b+\pi+a),S*sin(b+\pi+a)>
